This story has been updated. Shots were fired into the air Friday night at a shopping center in Loudoun County, authorities said. Several shots were fired near the 20700 block of Easthampton Plaza, at a shopping center south of Route 7, according to the county sheriffâ€™s office. No injuries were reported. The shots were fired by someone who was reportedly involved in a domestic dispute with a woman he knew, the office said. The woman took the gun from the man, who then fled, the office said. A gun was recovered, and a search was underway. The place where the shots were fired was identified by authorities as One Loudoun, described on its website as a mixed-use community in the heart of the county. It was unclear late Friday how many people saw the incident or heard the gunshots. 